“As it stands, Consol is only able to accommodate about 90 to 95% of the elevated total demand. So, this is a big risk for us, because it means that taverners had to be subjected to rationing of products, as manufacturers cannot really fill the liquids into the glass that is not even available. So, there is a big risk, but we are comforted by the fact that Consol has done all they could to make sure that they come back online come May when the Nigel plant is fully operational.” Glass shortage affects the liquor industry: 